DLink - Documentation
---------------------

What is DLink
=============
DLink is a small tool to connect your DServer to any IRC channel you want.
DLink establishes the connection between DServer and the IRC-Server and
simply logs in another user which is then used to provide communication
between DServer and the IRC channel.

Usage
=====
Before you can start DLink, you have to start your DServer.  After DServer
is running, simply start DLink, it will then connect to a default IRC
Server on a default channel.

DLink accepts some shell arguments to override the default values.
The template is:
IS=IRCSERVER/K,IRCP=IRCPORT/K/N,IRCC=IRCCHANNEL/K,LP=LOCALPORT/K/N,N=NICK/K

Explaination follows.

IRCSERVER or IS - Specify the IRC-Server DLink should connect to.  
                  Default:  irc.amigazeux.de

IRCPORT or IRCP - Specify the port on which DLink should connect to the
                  IRC-Server.  Default:  6667

IRCCHANNEL or IRCC - Specify on which channel DLink should log in.
                     Default: #dlink

LOCALPORT or LP - Specify on which port your DServer runs.
                  Default: 6318

NICK or N - Specify the nickname DLink should use on the IRC-Server.
            Default: DLink
